==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trigraph
<hw>Tri"graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>tri-</ets> + <ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety> <def>Three letters united in
pronunciation so as to have but one sound, or to form but one syllable,
as <xex>-ieu</xex> in <xex>adieu</xex>; a triphthong.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trigyn</ent>⟦br⟧
